.git/
.awman/
aspec/

# Language-client workspaces and docs: no Dockerfile (plain, .max, or .dev)
# COPYs these from the build context, so they are pure context bloat for every
# image. They also carry huge vendored trees (client-rust/target alone is
# ~1GB) whose sheer size + symlinks make Apple `container`'s context packer
# truncate the stream partway through the walk and mark itself DONE — dropping
# everything alphabetically after it (server/, max/, docker/) so their COPYs
# fail with "not found". Excluding the dirs outright keeps the packer from ever
# descending into them. Dev/test runs mount the repo as a volume, not via the
# build context, so this does not affect `make shell`/`test`/`check-static`.
client-python/
client-rust/
client-typescript/
docs/
# Build outputs and local state (rebuilt inside the image or irrelevant to it)
**/target/
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
# Test/tooling caches: rebuilt on every run, never wanted in the image, and —
# because tools rewrite them in place — a live `pytest`/`npm` run can mutate
# one mid-transfer and abort the context stream ("error from sender:
# archive/tar: invalid tar header"). Exclude them so the build can't race it.
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.coverage
*.db
*.db-*
.env
.env.*
data/
# macOS metadata: Finder droppings and AppleDouble resource-fork files. They
# carry extended-attribute data the Apple `container` context packer can encode
# into malformed PAX tar headers ("error from sender: archive/tar: invalid tar
# header"). Never wanted in a Linux image regardless.
**/.DS_Store
**/._*
